characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Mountjoy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Devon and Gloucestershire; of Norman origin): habitational name, ultimately from <i>Montjoie</i>, a crusaders’ name derived from that of the mountain in Palestine from which the first view of Jerusalem was obtained. The name was adopted for several places in western Europe (notably Montjoie-Saint-Martin in Manche), and this, or the original, could have given rise to the English surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Montjoy","meanings":["Altered form of English   Mountjoy  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William de Mountjoy was born in 1241, in Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Ralph Mountjoy. He married Andicitia de Vivonne in 1260, in Mountjoy, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1298, in his hometown, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1241–1298":"1241–1298","1248–1300":"1248–1300","1261–1318":"1261–1318","1263–Male":"1263–Surnud","1265–Male":"1265–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1248":"1248","1300":"1300","1298":"1298","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1263":"1263","1261":"1261","1260":"1260","about 1265":"umbes 1265","1318":"1318","about 1263":"umbes 1263","Mountjoy, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Mountjoy, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mountjoy, Hampshire, England":"Mountjoy, Hampshire, England","Mountjoy, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1241–1298":"1241–1298","1248–1300":"1248–1300","1261–1318":"1261–1318","1263–Male":"1263–Kuollut","1265–Male":"1265–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1248":"1248","1300":"1300","1298":"1298","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1263":"1263","1261":"1261","1260":"1260","about 1265":"noin 1265","1318":"1318","about 1263":"noin 1263","Mountjoy, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Mountjoy, Hampshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Mountjoy, Hampshire, England":"Mountjoy, Hampshire, England","Mountjoy, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1241–1298":"1241–1298","1248–1300":"1248–1300","1261–1318":"1261–1318","1263–Male":"1263–Décédé","1265–Male":"1265–Décédé","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1248":"1248","1300":"1300","1298":"1298","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1263":"1263","1261":"1261","1260":"1260","about 1265":"environ 1265","1318":"1318","about 1263":"environ 1263","Mountjoy, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Mountjoy, Hampshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Mountjoy, Hampshire, England":"Mountjoy, Hampshire, Angleterre","Mountjoy, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Sir William de Mountjoy est né 